      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TARTAN TIGER (9) is left the one to beat. Found two better at Wyong on debut before being heavily bet and narrowly beaten on a deep track over 1400m at Orange. Made up a stack of ground and draws inside today. HAMMURABI (4) can show more over the longer trip. Fronts up on a 7-day return and maps well. Penza sticks and he should be right in it. YESGLENN (3) has been finding it hard to break through at the provincials. Tries hard and is fit. He can make a place in this line-up. VINCENTVANGEE (6) is third-up and can show more with the blinkers going on for the first time. Has the inside gate and this is easier than Newcastle.",
